org.jsapar.parse

Class AbstractParseTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jsapar.parse.AbstractParseTask
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, ErrorEventListener, LineEventListener, ParseTask
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BeanParseTask, TextParseTask, XmlParseTask

    public abstract class AbstractParseTask
extends Object
implements ParseTask, LineEventListener, ErrorEventListener
    Abstract implementation of ParseTask interface. Provides possibility to have line event listeners and error event listeners. Override this class to implement a specific parser.

        Description copied from interface: ParseTask

      • errorEvent

        public void errorEvent(ErrorEvent event)
        Description copied from interface: ErrorEventListener

        Called when there is an error while parsing input or composing output. If an implementation of this method throws an unchecked exception, the parsing/composing will be aborted and the exception will be passed through to the original calling method.

        May throw unchecked exceptions depending on implementation.

        Specified by:
        errorEvent in interface ErrorEventListener
        Parameters:
        event - The event that contains the error information.
